Description: Convex ring foot and floor sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery skyphos; glazed black inside and out; foot glazed save stand ring; scraped groove on upper face of foot at base of wall; underside reserved with dot and two rings at centre; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 541)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1275)
